---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Harmonium from '../../components/Harmonium.astro';
---
<Layout title="Daily Riyaaz Practice Routine | Harmonium Halt"
  description="A proven 30-minute daily practice routine for consistent harmonium progress. Free harmonium lesson with interactive web harmonium tool.">
  <div class="bg-white border-b" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <a href="/lessons">Lessons</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <span>Daily Riyaaz Practice Routine</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-practice capitalize">practice</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.4);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">⏱ 30 min · Practice Module</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="section-title text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Daily Riyaaz Practice Routine</h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.6);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">A proven 30-minute daily practice routine for consistent harmonium progress.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-5 mb-6 border" style="background:#fef9f0;border-color:rgba(212,146,10,.25)">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-sm mb-3" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">📌 Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Riyaaz = disciplined daily practice — the foundation of all progress</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>20 min daily is more valuable than 3 hrs on weekends</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Always warm up before fast practice</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>End each session with free creative playing</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Track progress in a practice journal</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-hm">
      <h2>The Importance of Riyaaz</h2>
      <p>The word riyaaz means disciplined regular practice. In Indian classical music riyaaz is not optional — it is the entire path. The great masters practiced 6 to 8 hours daily for decades. While you may not match that commitment even 20 to 30 minutes of focused daily practice will produce remarkable results over months and years of consistent effort.</p>

      <h2>The 30-Minute Structure</h2>
      <p>Minutes 0 to 5: Warm-up with very slow ascending and descending scales in Sa equals C. Loosen fingers and establish steady bellows rhythm. Minutes 5 to 15: Alankar practice — choose 2 or 3 patterns and drill them at slow then medium tempo. Minutes 15 to 22: Current lesson focus — whatever you are actively learning this week. Minutes 22 to 28: Song or composition practice. Minutes 28 to 30: Free play and creative exploration.</p>

      <h2>Weeks 1 to 4 Foundation</h2>
      <p>First month focus: Master ascending and descending scales perfectly. Learn Alankars 1 through 4. Practice singing swara names while playing. End of month goal: play the full scale ascending and descending without errors at 80 BPM from memory with eyes closed. This foundation is what everything else builds upon.</p>

      <h2>Weeks 5 to 12 Skill Building</h2>
      <p>Months 2 and 3 focus: All 10 alankars at gradually increasing tempos. Learn your first bhajan to performance standard. Begin studying one raga's aroha avaroha and pakad. End of period goal: perform a complete bhajan without notation and play the aroha and avaroha of one raga from memory.</p>

      <h2>Tracking and Motivating Progress</h2>
      <p>Keep a practice journal. After each session write what you practiced for how long what felt easy and what needs more work. Review weekly to identify patterns. Celebrate milestones — your first clean scale your first complete bhajan your first raga phrase played correctly. Progress in music is real and tangible and worth explicitly acknowledging.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Practice Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-4" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Apply what you just learned on the interactive harmonium below.</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c1008,#3d1a08)">
        <Harmonium/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-stretch xs:items-center justify-between gap-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
      <a href="/lessons" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;text-decoration:none">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        All Lessons
      </a>
      <a href="/practice" class="btn-primary justify-center text-center">Open Full Practice Tool →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>